                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d220">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">851D.20/36b: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Brazil</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Caffery</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1943-03-18T12:00:00-04:00"
                            >March 18, 1943—noon</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>986. From the Under Secretary. Please express to Aranha<note n="31"
                        xml:id="d220fn31">Oswaldo Aranha, Brazilian Minister for Foreign
                        Affairs.</note> my confident belief that he will share with me a feeling of
                    approval and gratification at the action of the Governor of French Guiana in
                    placing his Government at the side of the United Nations through his adherence
                    to General Giraud, a step which clearly expresses the will of the people of this
                    French colony. [Welles.]</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Hull</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
